The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 1: A day after drug maker Sun Pharma made an open offer to fully acquire Taro Pharmaceutical, the Israeli firm said it would evaluate the unsolicited tender and advised its shareholders not to take any action immediately. The board of directors would meet to consider Suns offer in due course, Taro said.                            
	 New Delhi, July 1: Market regulator Sebi has exempted certain categories of investors, including officials from central and state governments and those appointed by the courts, from mandatory presentation of the permanent account number for transactions in the securities market.                            
	 Mumbai, July 1: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) will invest Rs 4,467 crore as capital expenditure in the current financial year, TCS chairman Ratan Tata said.                             
	 New Delhi, July 1: Iran today indicated that it might be willing to change the delivery point of gas it wanted to sell to India through a pipeline via Pakistan, but wanted New Delhi and Islamabad to decide quickly on the $7.4-billion project.                            
	 New Delhi, July 1: Finance minister P. Chidambaram today said the government would contain the fiscal deficit below its budget estimates of 2.5 per cent of GDP for the year.                                                                                                                         
